key "Takken:1999ez,Verhulst:2011ko,Qiu:2006ei"

\end_inset

.
 Male moths use specialised, equisitely sensitive neurons on their antenna
 to detect trace amounts of phereonome realeased by female moths up to 200
 m away and reach them in a few minutes 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Wall:1987hb,Kennedy:1974tx"

\end_inset

.
 Insects – either as pests or pollinators of crops – play a large role human
 welfare and olfaction plays a key role in their behavior.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The study of insect olfaction spans a number of broad questions spanning
 many discplines.
 What are the possible chemical signals that can be detected in the environment
 that insects inhabit? What are the molecules and cells that insects use
 to sense these signals? What are the challenges in signal detection and
